    cellular: { title: "Pathophysiology of Infertility Workup: Female & Male Factor Evaluation", content: "The nurse practitioner manages Infertility Workup: Female & Male Factor Evaluation through advanced understanding of maternal-fetal physiology, obstetric pathology, and evidence-based perinatal care. Assessment includes comprehensive obstetric history (gravidity, parity, previous pregnancy complications, gestational age determination), focused physical examination (fundal height measurement, fetal heart rate auscultation, cervical assessment when indicated, blood pressure and edema assessment), and interpretation of prenatal diagnostic studies (routine prenatal labs, glucose challenge test and OGTT for gestational diabetes, Group B Streptococcus screening, fetal ultrasound biometry and anatomy, non-stress test and biophysical profile interpretation). The NP applies evidence-based screening guidelines for prenatal genetic screening, manages common pregnancy complications (hyperemesis gravidarum, gestational diabetes, hypertensive disorders of pregnancy, preterm labor), prescribes medications with consideration of teratogenic risk (FDA pregnancy categories, individual drug safety data), and determines appropriate timing and criteria for obstetric consultation and hospital transfer. Postpartum care includes assessment for hemorrhage, infection, mood disorders (Edinburgh Postnatal Depression Scale screening), breastfeeding support, contraception counseling, and management of postpartum complications. The NP provides preconception counseling including folic acid supplementation, medication optimization, and chronic disease management for pregnancy planning." },
